ratings.rComments: This professor is utterly useless.

Very opinionated and closed-minded when it comes to other people's views. Overall, the class was simple, as long as you attend class and do the assignments. But don't expect compensation if you miss an assignment or any other points.
Lectures are not compulsory. All slides are posted online. Professor is very helpful and approachable. Teaching in class is also good and a little lively. Easy course. Recommended.

shes a pretty entertaining professor... lectures were somewhat helpful if you didn't know what was going on. Study past exams, review powerpoint slides and you'll be golden. MPs are fairly easy, and she's (and TAs) are always willing to help (and even give you the answers!) Easy A
Good teacher lectures are boring but helpful. MPs are a pain but helpful. Tests are tricky

Prof. Woodbury is so funny, she cracks me up every time i go to lecture! She is so random, and she is funnier if you pretend that she is a big grass smoker. The MPs take FOREVER if you are not computer-brained like me, but you will eventaully figure it out.  The tests are really hard because they try to trick you. i got a B

Woodbury is quite goofy.  However, pretty easy class.  Although normally worthless, the lectures give hints as to what is expected to show up on tests and MPs.  MPs are time consuming but for sure do-able.  I will never use coding again in my life..but found the class pretty simple and somewhat enjoyable.
Utterly useless professor. Didn't know how to code her way out of a paper bag. The MPs were insanely easy and the entire class is a blow-off. If you manage to get below an A, college isn't for you.
Class was great, other than the fact that it ran for 2 hours and was boring. At least the students were social in the small (30 student) setting.
She is a very difficult teacher and bitter. Make sure you attend class. Key to this class is mps. Final was easy, but still the hardest class i've taken.

Woodbury is kind of out there. Would always give us weekly updates on sports scores. Go to lectures when you can. Online homeworks are easy. Make sure you have a good group for MP. You have control over how well you do on exams. Study old exams. Should be able to pull off an B/A.

I love Professor Woodbury! I went to Gambill's lecture but would usually email Professor Woodbury when I had trouble on MPs or difficulty with material. She always writes back (usually extremely fast as well!) in detail explaining what needed to be done or what was done incorrectly. So helpful!
The class was not bad. The lecture are not mandatory but I would suggest going if you want a good grade. STUDY THE PREVIOUS EXAMS! It will really help you.
an awful class. the lectures are utterly pointless. this is one of the classes that i gained nothing out of. i highly recommend not taking this class. Also, the prof. is horrible...
Don't skip class and say you'll read the course guide cuz u won't - go to class, pay attention in class, Go to office hours for the MPs, and do some old tests and you'll be fine.
Great teacher, very helpful tho lectures tend to be boring

I don't see what's so hard about this class. If you go to lecture and your lab session, you should at least get a B. Mayne exam questions try to trick you so pay attention to what happens when the code is wrong and details such as that. The quizzes online are easy points. I only used/needed the lecture notes out of all the books.

I used to go to Gambill and it was a fun class, but I switched to Woodbury because she covers the material in a way I liked more.  I found I could concentrate better.  With her help and the awesome T.A's, I really enjoy the class!
Boring class, but easy if you know what's in the course guide.

She doesn't really know her material that well, which is too bad because it is somewhat interesting material.  The exams are very difficult multiple choice tests which will purposely try to trick you.  Kind of boring and has a tendency to ramble.
As far as CS goes, she may be the best teacher for computer idiots like me.  Did not seem to know  how to do the MP's though.
Boring, doesn't know own material herself.  Can't help very well b/c she doesn't know what she's talking about.  Messed up my grade at the end and doesn't know how to add!

Horrible class though you'll get an A.  She doesn't know the material and going to lecture is a total waste.  I agree the TA's are excellent, they know their stuff and they're pretty helpful.  Just think of this class as a GPA booster.

Yes, she is flighty and doesn't know the material as well as she should, but the class itself is easy! If you're not completely ignorant of computers and computing, you'll do fine. Tests are easy, you can work in groups on the MPs and can attempt the homeworks as much as you want. At least she tries to make class fun and interesting for everyone!

She is a terrible teacher. She takes at least 10 minutes to get started with each class. She doesn't explain things well. Class starts off easy then gets ridiculously hard towards the end. You don't learn stuff you need for the MP's until right before they are due.
I fall asleep often, but she teaches well. Her TA's are awesome.

This was a pretty easy class. It's mandatory for business majors. There are 2 tests, with the first one being the more difficult. THere are 6 MP's (Machine probelems that are done on the computers). These are the hardest portion of the class but the TA's are VERY helpful. She tried to keep the class interesting but the material just isn't interestn

Going to class is useless, she makes many mistakes and doesn't seem to know all that much about lecturing.  The MP's took awhile, but weren't hard.  I thought her tests were too tricky.  I got all A's on the MP's, but somehow would do awful on all of her tests.  And yes, I did all of the MP's by myself, I didn't cheat.

I really enjoyed this class, and the lectures were very helpful. First I thought they would be unnecessary but turns out they really are. She always answered my e-mails quickly, made sure I had my questions answered, and was very understanding. MPs are hard, but do-able, the tests are pretty tough.

She explains concepts well. Always ready to answer questions, and always responds to my inquiries quickly. As a teacher, she's great, but the class itself is damn hard. MP'S ARE KILLER, namely the last three. Test Q's are very tricky. This is class is no easy A.

What a complete moron!  She hates the cheif too.  She was never prepared for class and had trouble using simple applications like Excel.  I could have taught the class better.  When I went in for help she gave my work to other students.  She is a very offensive person and I reccomend taking Gambil- he is a much better teach and a better person.
Very flighty, but helpful and understanding. Def pay attention to your TA
cs105- i got an A
She's a very nice lady.  Her MPs can be quite tedious and sometimes difficult.  The content of the class is very helpful and valued in the work place.
I knew more about what she was talking about than she did.

Can't stand this woman and her constand bashing of the United States. If she doesnt like it, she should get out. Stop telling us. If Indians were angry with us because were self important, all of them would not be coming to our country.

1st MP takes 5 mins. 2nd MP takes 30 mins. 3rd=>1hr...4/5/6 MPs = DEATH! better find a good programmer to be your partner Exams are ok if you do the pratice exams in CoursePacket 8am Lectures...Don't go! complete waste of time, you won't remember a thing from it
Absent-minded, disorganized, but nice. Class is easy. She did go over some MP stuff, she just didn't give real easy answers. TAs are the greatest asset though to this class.

This class isn't so much hard as it is irritating. Prof. Woodbury is actually nice and open with the students, but she shows little competence during her demos. She could admittedly be more insightful and clearer, but this class really requires a good deal of self-teaching. Try and find a good TA.

it's absolutely ridiculous that lecturer woodbury makes the tests for prof. gambill's sections of CS105, especially since these tests are incoherent and nit-picky. she controls my grade with her tests but i've never actually even seen her. it's quite a creepy feeling;)

Don't go to lecture, it's useless especially at 9 am on mondays and wednesdays.  you'll find better things to do, like sleep. Make sure you go to the labs though, they are helpful since they are taught by TA's and not her. Also start your MP's early they take a lot of time.
terrible
the worst class!

Prof. Woodbury does not come to class prepared and as a result, she has no idea what she is talking about.  She goes over the easy concepts too much.  The TA's help a lot, especially with the MPs. Go into TA office hours for help - and if you're TA isn't helpful, definitely go one of the other ones.

Lectures are not applicable to the MPs at all.  Poking my eyes out with a dull pencil would be preferable to attending the 8 am lectures.  Good luck!  Start the MPs early and make friends with your TA.
This is the worst teacher i have run into at this University, she should be fired. If it wasnt for her TA's the class would go to hell
No Comments

ok the only reason i took this class is cuz it's a requirement. supposedly it's supposed to be a joke if you have the other professor. i think the class is hard because she doesn't know how to teach it. she's nice as hell but a poor professor.

They let anyone teach these days. She seems like a nice person, however, she's a teacher, and I haven't learned one single thing in the class yet (It's the week before finals). Her examples never work,and she has to ask the TA everything. 2 thumbs down!!
Talk about boring, she treats you like a middle schooler, going over easy stuff to the point of death.
Thank god this class is so easy because this woman is as DUMB AS A PILE OF ROCKS
I think she knows what she's talking about, but she's got a crappy way of conveying it. Go to the TAs for help because she's definately a little nuts
No Comments
This lady is eye candy.  She is my inspiration for getting up at 8 am.  Watching this babe teach is better than a bowl of Wheaties for starting your day.
Essays seems easy, but they grade kinda hard. Otherwise class is a enjoyable walk in the park.
pretty straightforward.  easy class, but very very boring.
